cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF 

This paper is focused on the performance analysis of two competing technologies for vehicle to vehicle communication in intelligent transport systems. The paper uses mathematical models based on discrete time Markov chains to study the medium access control layer performance of the two technologies. This makes it likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses collision resolution and performance enhancements, which could make it relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Performance (cs.PF) sub-categories.
